{"lemma":"نِيّاتٌ","slug":"نِيّاتٌ","root":"ن.#.#","root_slug":"ن-_-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ن-_-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n44212"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%86%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%91%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of نَوَى (nawā, “to think, to intend”) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"intention, purpose, resolution","examples":[{"text":"إِنَّمَا الْأَعْمَالُ بِالنِّيَّاتِ، وَإِنَّمَا لِكُلِّ ٱمْرِئٍ مَا نَوَى","english":"But deeds are in intentions, and every man will have what he intends."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"will, tendency, inclination, wish, object of investigation"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"distance","tags":["obsolete"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Classical Syriac ܢܹܐ (nē, “please”) and Hebrew נָא (ná, “please (adverb), if you please”)."},"ipa":["/nij.ja/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n44212","headword_ar":"نِيَّةٌ","root":"nwY","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An intention, an intent, a purpose, a design, an aim; a determination of the mind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heart:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA:) this is the general meaning: (Msb:) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"direction that one takes"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a journey,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"near or distant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in an action:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thing that one intends,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"purposes,"},{"kind"